notesStmt.note: In Latin with Latin and Greek marginalia.
Manuscript on large imperial size paper.
Ricci, S. de. Census of medieval and Renaissance manuscripts in the United States and Canada, SM.16

msContents.summary: Contains Suetonius' Lives of the Twelve Caesars, preceded by an epigram on Julius Caesar by fourth century Roman poet, Ausonius.

msItem.title: De vita XII Caesarum manuscript, ca. 1470? / C. Suetonii Tranquilli.
msItem.author: Suetonius, ca. 69-approximately 122, author.

respStmt.persName: Allen, Henry Ellis, 1807 or 1808- former owner.
Smedley, William T. (William Thomas), 1851-1934, former owner.
Folger, Emily C. J. (Emily Clara Jordan), 1858-1936, former owner.

msItem.title: Liber I, D[ivus] C[aius] Iulius Caes[ar] Imp[erator]

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 33 long lines (dimensions of written space: 190 x 125 mm); above first line; machine-ruled, with horizontal lines in ink and vertical lines in lead.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a very high quality western-style Greek hand.

decoDesc.decoNote: Decorated initial framed in gold (leaf 1r); Penwork initials for each chapter alternate in red and blue ink.

binding.p: Bound in 18th century burnished calf with gold tooling; on spine in gold: Suetonius Tranquillu -- Codex Chartaceus; gilt edges.

origin.p: Written in Italy, ca. 1470 (De Ricci); circa 1470?

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Rev. Henry Drury; Henry Allen (Henrici Alani--bookplate); and W.T. Smedley; Purchased as part of the Smedley Collection in 1924 by Henry Clay Folger.
